title: St. Catherine of Siena invites you to 'Pumpkin Patch' sale
text: St. Catherine of Siena Youth Ministry The St. Catherine of Siena Youth Ministry celebrates the fall season with its "Pumpkin Patch" sale from 10 a.m. to 6 p.m. Oct. 17-31 at St. Catherine of Siena Catholic Church, 745 W. Main St. in West Dundee. All proceeds will support the St. Catherine of Siena Youth Ministry. "Over 60 volunteers unloaded a truckload of 2,200 pumpkins of all sizes and hundreds of gourds in five hours to get ready for our fall 'Pumpkin Patch' fun," said Deacon Hank Schmalen of St. Catherine of Siena Catholic Church. Bring the family to a special Pumpkin Festival at the church grounds on Sunday, Oct. 18, from 12:30 to 4:30 p.m. Activities include story time, face painting, bake sale and more. For information, call the parish office at (847) 426-2217 or visit parish.st-cath.net . Share this page
